physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Tender ulcerations varying in size and shape scattered on both legs; hypopigmented scars with changes of atrophie blanche noted. Normal ankle and brachial indices and Doppler indices; mildly to moderately decreased transcutaneous oximetry measurements in both legs and feet. Venous studies normal with no evidence of venous incompetence or obstruction.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: After initiating warfarin therapy, the patient's ulcers healed within 2 months and remained healed 3 years later, with no new ulcerations developed.
